All four sources produce defects classified using the unified taxonomy
from Layer 1: category (8 types), severity (4 levels), and member impact
scope (3 levels). The dashboard does not re-classify---it displays the
classification assigned at the source.

3\. Dashboard Views

The dashboard is structured as three views, each designed for a specific
audience and decision type. All three views operate on the same
underlying data; they differ in aggregation level and what they
emphasize.

3.1 Command View (Primary)

The Command View is the default landing screen. It provides an instant
health assessment that any authorized user can read in under five
seconds. This view answers: "Is the system healthy right now, and if
not, what's the most critical issue?"

Status Banner

A full-width banner at the top of the screen with three possible states:

  ----------- ------------- ------------------------ ----------------------
  **State**   **Color**     **Meaning**              **Trigger Condition**

  **GREEN**   Green         All systems nominal. All Zero P0/P1 defects AND
              background,   tests passing. No        last build passed AND
              white text    Critical or High open    data quality scan \<
                            defects. Data quality    24 hours old
                            scan current.            

  **AMBER**   Amber         Issues exist that        Any P2 defect \> 0 OR
              background,   require attention but    data quality scan \>
              dark text     are not blocking member  48 hours OR coverage
                            benefit processing.      regression detected

  **RED**     Red           Critical issue. Benefit  Any P0 or P1 defect
              background,   processing may be        open OR any demo case
              white text    affected. Immediate      failing OR any
                            investigation required.  acceptance test
                                                     failing
  ----------- ------------- ------------------------ ----------------------

When the banner is RED, it includes a one-line summary of the most
critical open defect, directly actionable: e.g., "P0: Tier 1 benefit
calculation uses 1.5% multiplier instead of 2.0% --- affects all Tier 1
members --- opened 2 hours ago."

Four Canary Cards

Below the banner, four cards represent the four demo cases. Each card
shows:

-   **Member name and case description** (e.g., "Martinez --- Tier 1,
    Rule of 75")

-   **Status indicator:** green checkmark (last acceptance test passed)
    or red X (failed)

-   **Last verified:** timestamp of the most recent passing acceptance
    test

-   **Key verification points:** the two or three most critical values
    from the hand calculation (e.g., "AMS: \$8,542.33 ✓ \| Benefit:
    \$4,899.34 ✓ \| 75% J&S: \$4,482.85 ✓")

These four cards are the most important thing on the dashboard. If all
four are green, the system's core calculations are correct. If any is
red, something fundamental is broken.

Defect Summary Counters

A row of counters showing the current defect inventory by priority:

  -------------- -------------- -------------- -------------- --------------
  **P0 ---       **P1 ---       **P2 ---       **P3 ---       **P4 ---
  STOP**         Immediate**    Urgent**       Standard**     Backlog**

  Target: 0      Target: 0      Target: \< 5   Target: \< 15  No limit
  -------------- -------------- -------------- -------------- --------------

Each counter is clickable, drilling into the filtered defect list for
that priority level.

